## RELEASE WORKFLOW

```bash
# 1. Verify you own the paths you're modifying
cat OWNERSHIP.yaml | grep -A10 "YourAgentName"

# 2. Make changes (only to paths you own!)

# 3. Update VERSION
echo "1.6.16" > VERSION

# 4. Commit and tag
git add -A && git commit -m "feat: description"
git tag v1.6.16 && git push origin main --tags

# 5. Create release
gh release create v1.6.16 --title "v1.6.16" --notes "See CHANGELOG"
```

## IF YOU NEED TO MODIFY A PATH YOU DON'T OWN

1. **Ask the human**: "I need to modify `<path>` but it's owned by `<owner>`. Should I proceed?"

2. **Or file an issue**:
   ```bash
   gh issue create --repo afctony64/<owner-repo> \
     --title "Request: Modify <path> in pom-config" \
     --body "Description of needed change..."
   ```

## BREAKING CHANGES

Coordinate with app teams BEFORE making breaking changes:
```bash
gh issue create --repo afctony64/PomAI --title "BREAKING: ..."
gh issue create --repo afctony64/Pomothy --title "BREAKING: ..."
```
